<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showMessage?topicID=1232.topic">Has anyone consistenly landed wrath of the elements?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Other threads are either aged from the first twenty pages, or have inobvious titles and escaped my search.<br>
<br>
Here is another example.  Long ago, when I was 49th level, I hunted baraccudas beneath the placid waters of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Lake of Ill Manners</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  At the time, I was spec'd in evocation.  Using the 49 fire pet against the cudas, I had to be certain that I did not take aggro from my pet, especially as it was not rooting.<br>
<br>
I had two relevent spells available to me at that time, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Shock_of_Swords.htm">Shock of Swords</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Elemental_Maelstrom.htm">Elemental Maelstrom</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Swords</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does 600 damage for 250 mana, base DPM 2.4, or with 50% spec conj, for 244 mana or 2.46 DPM.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Maelstrom</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does 250 initial damage, plus 70 per tick for five ticks, or 600 damage total, for 240 mana, or with 200% spec evoc, 216 mana, for 2.78 DPM.  It does not break root, when that is relevant, and causes less aggro than shock.<br>
<br>
In addition, when the target is not moving at all during a tick, a DoT does a third more damage per tick.  So assuming the fight is static, which it was, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Maelstrom</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does a total of 250 + (5 * 70 * 4/3) = 717 damage for 216 mana, or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3.32 damage per mana</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
When do mages get a nuke with an effective 3.32 DPM ratio?  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Scars_of_Sigil.htm">Scars of Sigil</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for an evocation mage with a damage bracer does about 500 damage for 158 mana, or 3.17 DPM, oops, not quite as good, and is level 54, and includes a focus item.  Shucks.<br>
<br>
Oh, and if you read carefully, you will notice that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shock of Swords</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> saves versus Magic <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> +5</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, so it is resisted more.<br>
<br>
So we have two 44th level spells, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SoS</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> EM</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The DoT spell does 117 more damage for 28 less mana, is resisted less than the nuke of the same level, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>and</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> causes less aggro.<br>
<br>
And it sucks?<br>
<br>
As for the monster summoning line, prior to the massive pet upgrades, the MS line was essentially an earth elemental, same hit points, melee, and immunities, with one fifth of them with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> FireElemental Aura</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Considering what jokes the 50+ fire elementals are, if you were a post-50 non-epicked mage who previously like soloing with fire elementals, for most purposes, a MS pet was your strongest damage shielded pet.<br>
<br>
See:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showMessage?topicID=640.topic">Pet Hit Points - GVoc: Earth, Air, Water // MSIII /// Epic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showMessage?topicID=688.topic">MSII v.s. 49 Pets</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showMessage?topicID=487.topic">Monster Summoning 1 Rocks!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
