<br>
While it is sad that MS3 was not upgraded when the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Greater Vocarates</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> were, throughout most of its history, the monster summoning pets have been quite viable under the right circumstances.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alucard</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  dude, if you meant you get low agro associate on the dot so it won't attack you... <br>
just wait like few seconds before you nuke with char... or whatever nuke you have...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SkyFire</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> everything except spermies is immune to fire, so char, scars, etc., is pretty much out of the picture, and yes, I know how to manage aggro.  DoTs are one of the tools I use to manage aggro.  With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> KEI</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I was alternating the two dots, the boot nuke and the pet heal, never getting aggro, never breaking root, and bringing them down fairly quickly.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> KEI</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> lasts what, a couple hours?  And it only takes one broken root and aggro to get it dispelled.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alucard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  or if you meant that dot won't dispell the root of earth pet... <br>
