<br>
In <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SkyFire</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> yes, I have single targets, and rains should work.<br>
<br>
The point is that the mage DoTs are legitimate tools, they are <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;most horrific ideas of spell lines,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and there are working mages who make good use of these spells. They do not serve the same purpose for us that they do for the DoT dependent classes.  They are a special purpose tool, but a tool nonetheless.<br>
<br>
I don't use <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Monster Summoning 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> either, since the GV upgrades, and its a shame.  But some mages still get use out of these spells.<br>
