I find that I learn the most when I listen to play who play <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>differently</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that I do, and don't dismiss their strategies out of hand.  Even when they are flawed, I often can learn <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>something</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<br>
As for managing aggro, I find that under many circumstances, I can chain the dots and the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecalling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and never break root and get aggro.  This is against a variety of mobs, not just in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SkyFire</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  However, if instead I alternate the boots with the equivalent nuke, that is exactly what will happen.  The boots are a 17 second cast, and I have a few seconds between them to cast <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>one</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> spell.  I find alternating the dots works just fine, and has exactly the effect I want.  Alternating click nukes and real nukes does not.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alucard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  as for the goblins in LOIO<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Who said anything about goblins?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showMessage?topicID=54.topic">49-52ish: Lake Fillomen Baraccudas</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Six static single dark blue melee only spawns, each on two minute timer, and no competion?  Sweet for the 49-51st mage.  Used to solo these naked except for malachite between raid wipeout and CRs, just bind in FV.  In contrast, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bloodgill Goblins</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (or the Bee Gees, as they are affectionately known), are almost always contested.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Not all mages like chaining pets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alucard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  hahaha you are like saying not all of cleric will use CH because they may have a crapy modem and they usually let tanks die if that happens... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Hate to break the news to you, but despite the fact that chaining pets is very efficient, not all mages chain pets, or want to chain pets.  A poor connection is just <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>one</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> example while someone might prefer other techniques.  An epicked mage, for example, is loathe to chain pets.  Chaining pets takes a certain amount of skill and timing, which can be difficult without much summoning haste or its equivalent.  Some, epicked or not, enjoy a more leisurely and certain fight, with one pet, fully buffed, holding aggro all the time, simultaneous healing the pet while burning down the enemy.  Maybe they like to burn down their mana bar in a single encounter, then re-fill it by cannibalizing pets.  Maybe they like to set a pet up with summoned armor and maybe a pair of gnoll hide lariats to stun.<br>
<br>
Not everyone chains pets.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->   Dots never did 1/3 more damage if a mob wasn't moving they just did full damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->According to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Silverblade</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and many others, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showMessageRange?topicID=1350.topic&amp;start=21&amp;stop=31">If a DoTted mob is stationary, it takes an additional 1/3 damage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  This from the previously referenced thread on mage dots.<br>
<br>
Even without the additional 1/3 damage, for a 49th level evocation mage prior to focus items, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Maelstrom</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> causes at least as much damage for less mana, less aggro, and fewer resists.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Also EM and MoE break root. They have a DD component at the begining of them so it is a nuke with a dot component so it can break root.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Right.  And the larger the amount of damage, the greater the chance to break root.  Since the initial DD component of the DoTs is much smaller than doing all the damage up front using a nuke, the chance of breaking root is much less.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  So basically no matter what you do to explain it the dots are vastly inferior to mage dd spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Not really sure how many different ways there are to explain it to you, since you've made up your mind already.  The disadvantage of nukes over dots is that they generate more aggro and and more likely to break root.  The example I gave at the top of this post, alternating <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecalling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with dots, instead with nukes, and not getting aggro or breaking root is a real life working example where dots are a better solution than nukes.  Substituting a shock spell between boots does <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> work the same.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alurcard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  i never use that spell except to test it for fun..<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Never used the spell, huh, but your conclusion differs from those who actually use the spells, such as myself, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Redorius, Sawzalla, Adonhiram, Branven</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and others.  Maybe, just maybe, in the process of actually using the spells, they have discovered some advantages to a spell line that you have dismissed after a short time.<br>
<br>
I come to this board to learn from others, and to refine and share what I have learned.<br>
<br>
Maybe your first reaction to things like this should be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;perhaps..&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> instead of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;lol.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  You might just learn something new.  I know I have.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sage ArchMage Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
