<br>
Half right, half wrong - Raz is correct that motionless mobs get a server-side bonus to dot damage.  This happened in the very same patch that nerfed damage to mobs in motion.  However, since all of the spell sites (Castersrealm, Lucy, etc) list the pre-bonus damage for all dots (they did this for healing penalties too), it's usually forgotten.<br>
<br>
Here's the patch message discussing the *original* dot changes (nerfs/bonuses):<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/archives.asp?Day=13&Month=9&Year=1999&ID=286&Action=View">eq.crgaming.com/archives....ction=View</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> DoT spells have all had their duration slightly increased. If the monster moves for 18 seconds during a fight, it will take as much damage from the DoT as it would before the patch. If the monster moves for less then 18 seconds during a fight, your DoT will do more damage then it would have done before the patch. If the monster moves more then 18 seconds during the fight, it will take less damage then it would have before the patch.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
However, like I said, you are also half right - It doesn't do 1/3 more damage.  I don't have the exact numbers (they are in multiple threads on the Druid's Grove if you really want them), but it's more like 15%.<br>
